<p>SATA 2.6 first defined the slimline connector, intended for smaller form-factors; e.g., notebook optical drives.</p>
<p><br clear="all" /></p>
<p><a name="Micro_connector" id="Micro_connector"></a></p>
<h5><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Serial_ATA&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Micro connector">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Micro connector</span></h5>
<table class="wikitable" align="right" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0;">
<tr>
<th colspan="2">Pin #</th>
<th>Function</th>
</tr>
